Datafiniti Hotel-Reviews¶

Description
This dataset is a list of about 2,000 hotels and 10,000 reviews from Datafiniti's Business Database updated between January 2018 to September 2018.

Source
https://data.world/datafiniti/hotel-reviews

Business data schema
https://developer.datafiniti.co/docs/business-data-schema

  1. Import and examine the dataset
  2. Create fact and dim tables
  3. Write data pipeline script
  4. Load and visualize data

2. Create fact and dim tables¶

Introducing a lambda hash function, in SQL I usually use MD5 or something similar. For reasons of simplicity I skip the plumbing columns (dw_ins_upd_dts and dw_etl_run_num) as there is not really an incremental load here. However, this could be introduced with a later version.

I'm creating fact tables for the granular ratings:

  • fact_rating

as well as dim tables for users, states and hotels:

  • dim_user
  • dim_hotel
  • dim_state
  • dim_cal (just a basic one, the logic behind can be extended)

as well as aggregated fact tables for users, states and hotels:

  • fact_user
  • fact_state
  • fact_hotel
  • fact_rating_2 (that's the raw fact enlarged with all dims for python plotting, not really best practice, but convenient for plotting)

I did the aggregated fact tables for users, states and hotels just for demonstration purposes. Actually the same result could be achieved in reporting layer with fact_rating_2 table. It depends on the size of the dataset and to what degree the reports should be aggregated before the reporting. With this dataset we can do the visualization part also on fact_rating_2 table (which is unaggregated). It is always a matter of requirements.

I skip stages of the datawarehouse modeling chain due to lack of time and the lack of incremental data loads.

A chain could look like: STAGE_INC -> STAGE -> BASE -> PACKAGE / REPORTING

Usually the aggregations are done in PACKAGE / REPORTING stage..

convert_datetime_to_date = lambda x: datetime.datetime.strptime(x[:10], '%Y-%m-%d').date()
return_uppercase = lambda x: x.upper()
In [13]:
columns_fact_ratings_2=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL','REVIEWS_DATE', 'REVIEWS_DATESEEN', 'REVIEWS_RATING',
                        'REVIEWS_SOURCEURLS', 'REVIEWS_TEXT', 'REVIEWS_TITLE', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE']

df_fact_rating = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_fact_ratings_2)

df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'] =          (helper['id']+'_'+helper['reviews.username']+'_'+helper['reviews.date'])\
                                            .apply(hash_function)
df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL'] =    helper['id'].apply(hash_function)
df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER'] =     helper['reviews.username'].apply(hash_function)
df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'] =    (helper['province'].apply(return_uppercase)).apply(hash_function)

df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_DATE'] =        helper['reviews.date'].apply(convert_datetime_to_date).astype('datetime64[ns]')
df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_DATESEEN'] =    helper['reviews.dateSeen']
df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_RATING'] =      helper['reviews.rating'].astype(float)
df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_SOURCEURLS'] =  helper['reviews.sourceURLs']
df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_TEXT'] =        helper['reviews.text']
df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_TITLE'] =       helper['reviews.title']

def create_date_table(start='2010-01-01', end='2020-12-31'):
    df = pd.DataFrame({"CLDR_DATE": pd.date_range(start, end)})
    df["DAY_NAME"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.weekday_name
    df["WEEK"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.weekofyear
    df["QUARTER"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.quarter
    df["MONTH"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.month
    df["YEAR"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.year
    df["YEAR_HALF"] = (df.QUARTER + 1) // 2
    return df

df_dim_cal = create_date_table()

columns_fact_state=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', 'RATING_MEAN','RATING_STD', 'RATING_MIN', 'RATING_MAX', 'RATING_COUNT']

df_fact_state = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_fact_state)

df_fact_state['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'] = helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().index
df_fact_state['RATING_MEAN'] =          helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE')['REVIEWS_RATING'].mean().values
df_fact_state['RATING_STD'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().values
df_fact_state['RATING_MIN'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].min().values
df_fact_state['RATING_MAX'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].max().values
df_fact_state['RATING_COUNT'] =         helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].count().values

3. Write data pipeline script¶

There are multiple approaches for The Data Pipeline. One could use Tools like Talend or a framework like Airflow or Glue from AWS. I used Python libraries here to create a simple SQLite db file, with SQLAlchemy we can also connect, write, update and delete in MySQL or Postgres DBs. Here are the instructions for connecting to different types of databases using SQLAlchemy.

In [40]:
def data_pipeline(df_ratings, df_states):
    # functions
    hash_function = lambda x: hashlib.sha256(str(str(x)).encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()
    convert_datetime_to_date = lambda x: datetime.datetime.strptime(x[:10], '%Y-%m-%d').date()
    return_uppercase = lambda x: x.upper()
    area_in_mi2 = lambda x: int(x[:x.find(' ')].replace(',',''))
    area_in_km2 = lambda x: int(x[x.find(' ')+1:].replace(')','').replace('(','').replace(',',''))
    
    # fact_rating 
    columns_fact_ratings = ['id', 'reviews.date', 'reviews.dateSeen', 'reviews.rating', 'reviews.sourceURLs', 'reviews.text',
                            'reviews.title', 'reviews.username', 'sourceURLs', 'province']
    helper = df[columns_fact_ratings]
    
    columns_fact_ratings_2=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL','REVIEWS_DATE', 'REVIEWS_DATESEEN', 'REVIEWS_RATING',
                        'REVIEWS_SOURCEURLS', 'REVIEWS_TEXT', 'REVIEWS_TITLE', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE']
    df_fact_rating = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_fact_ratings_2)

    df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'] =          (helper['id']+'_'+helper['reviews.username']+'_'+helper['reviews.date'])\
                                                .apply(hash_function)
    df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL'] =    helper['id'].apply(hash_function)
    df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER'] =     helper['reviews.username'].apply(hash_function)
    df_fact_rating['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'] =    (helper['province'].apply(return_uppercase)).apply(hash_function)

    df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_DATE'] =        helper['reviews.date'].apply(convert_datetime_to_date).astype('datetime64[ns]')
    df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_DATESEEN'] =    helper['reviews.dateSeen']
    df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_RATING'] =      helper['reviews.rating'].astype(float)
    df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_SOURCEURLS'] =  helper['reviews.sourceURLs']
    df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_TEXT'] =        helper['reviews.text']
    df_fact_rating['REVIEWS_TITLE'] =       helper['reviews.title']
    
    # dim_user
    columns_dim_user = ['reviews.userCity', 'reviews.userProvince', 'reviews.username']
    helper = df[columns_dim_user]

    columns_dim_user_2=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY', 'USER_NAME', 'USER_CITY', 'USER_PROVINCE']

    df_dim_user = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_dim_user_2)

    df_dim_user['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'] =  helper['reviews.username'].apply(hash_function)
    df_dim_user['USER_NAME'] =       helper['reviews.username']
    df_dim_user['USER_CITY'] =       helper['reviews.userCity']
    df_dim_user['USER_PROVINCE'] =   helper['reviews.userProvince']
    df_dim_user.drop_duplicates(subset=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'],inplace=True)
    
    # dim_hotel
    columns_dim_hotel = [ 'id',  'dateAdded', 'dateUpdated', 'address', 'categories', 'primaryCategories', 'city', 
                     'country', 'latitude', 'longitude', 'name', 'postalCode', 'province']
    helper = df[columns_dim_hotel]

    columns_dim_hotel_2=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY', 'DATE_ADDED', 'DATE_UPDATED', 'ADDRESS', 'CATEGORIES', 'PRIMARY_CATEGORIES', 'CITY', 
                     'COUNTRY', 'LATITUDE', 'LONGITUDE', 'NAME_HOTEL', 'POSTAL_CODE', 'DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE']
    df_dim_hotel = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_dim_hotel_2)

    df_dim_hotel['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'] =  helper['id'].apply(hash_function)
    df_dim_hotel['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'] =  (helper['province'].apply(return_uppercase)).apply(hash_function)

    df_dim_hotel['DATE_ADDED'] =          helper['dateAdded'].apply(convert_datetime_to_date)
    df_dim_hotel['DATE_UPDATED'] =        helper['dateUpdated'].apply(convert_datetime_to_date)
    df_dim_hotel['ADDRESS'] =             helper['address']
    df_dim_hotel['CATEGORIES'] =          helper['categories']
    df_dim_hotel['PRIMARY_CATEGORIES'] =  helper['primaryCategories']
    df_dim_hotel['CITY'] =                helper['city']
    df_dim_hotel['COUNTRY'] =             helper['country']
    df_dim_hotel['LATITUDE'] =            helper['latitude']
    df_dim_hotel['LONGITUDE'] =           helper['longitude']
    df_dim_hotel['NAME_HOTEL'] =          helper['name']
    df_dim_hotel['POSTAL_CODE'] =         helper['postalCode']
    df_dim_hotel.drop_duplicates(subset=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'],inplace=True)
    
    # dim_state
    columns_dim_state = list(df_states.columns)
    helper = df_states

    columns_dim_state_2=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY', 'NAME_STATE', 'ABBREVIATION', 'CAPITAL', 'LARGEST_CITY', 'STATEHOOD', 'POPULATION_EST', 'TOTAL_AREA_IN_MI2',
                     'TOTAL_AREA_IN_KM2', 'LAND_AREA_IN_MI2', 'LAND_AREA_IN_KM2', 'WATER_AREA_IN_MI2', 'WATER_AREA_IN_KM2']
    df_dim_state = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_dim_state_2)

    df_dim_state['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'] =      helper['Abbr.'].apply(hash_function)

    df_dim_state['NAME_STATE'] =          helper['State']
    df_dim_state['ABBREVIATION'] =        helper['Abbr.']
    df_dim_state['CAPITAL'] =             helper['Capital']
    df_dim_state['LARGEST_CITY'] =        helper['Largest city']
    df_dim_state['STATEHOOD'] =           helper['Statehood']
    df_dim_state['POPULATION_EST'] =      helper['Population est.']
    df_dim_state['TOTAL_AREA_IN_MI2'] =   helper['Total area in mi2 (km2)'].apply(area_in_mi2)
    df_dim_state['TOTAL_AREA_IN_KM2'] =   helper['Total area in mi2 (km2)'].apply(area_in_km2)
    df_dim_state['LAND_AREA_IN_MI2'] =    helper['Land area in mi2 (km2)'].apply(area_in_mi2)
    df_dim_state['LAND_AREA_IN_KM2'] =    helper['Land area in mi2 (km2)'].apply(area_in_km2)
    df_dim_state['WATER_AREA_IN_MI2'] =   helper['Water area in mi2 (km2)'].apply(area_in_mi2)
    df_dim_state['WATER_AREA_IN_KM2'] =   helper['Water area in mi2 (km2)'].apply(area_in_km2)
    
    # dim_cal
    def create_date_table(start='2010-01-01', end='2020-12-31'):
        df = pd.DataFrame({"CLDR_DATE": pd.date_range(start, end)})
        df["DAY_NAME"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.weekday_name
        df["WEEK"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.weekofyear
        df["QUARTER"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.quarter
        df["MONTH"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.month
        df["YEAR"] = df.CLDR_DATE.dt.year
        df["YEAR_HALF"] = (df.QUARTER + 1) // 2
        return df

    df_dim_cal = create_date_table()
    
    # fact_user
    helper = pd.merge(df_fact_rating, df_dim_user, how='left', left_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER'], right_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'])

    columns_fact_user=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', 'RATING_MEAN','RATING_STD', 'RATING_MIN', 'RATING_MAX', 'RATING_COUNT']
    df_fact_user = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_fact_user)

    df_fact_user['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER'] =  helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().index
    df_fact_user['RATING_MEAN'] =          helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER')['REVIEWS_RATING'].mean().values
    df_fact_user['RATING_STD'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().values
    df_fact_user['RATING_MIN'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].min().values
    df_fact_user['RATING_MAX'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].max().values
    df_fact_user['RATING_COUNT'] =         helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].count().values
    df_fact_user.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)
    
    # fact_state
    helper = pd.merge(df_fact_rating, df_dim_state, how='left', left_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'], right_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'])

    columns_fact_state=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', 'RATING_MEAN','RATING_STD', 'RATING_MIN', 'RATING_MAX', 'RATING_COUNT']
    df_fact_state = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_fact_state)

    df_fact_state['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'] = helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().index
    df_fact_state['RATING_MEAN'] =          helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE')['REVIEWS_RATING'].mean().values
    df_fact_state['RATING_STD'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().values
    df_fact_state['RATING_MIN'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].min().values
    df_fact_state['RATING_MAX'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].max().values
    df_fact_state['RATING_COUNT'] =         helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].count().values
    
    # fact_hotel
    helper = pd.merge(df_fact_rating, df_dim_hotel, how='left', left_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL'], right_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'])

    columns_fact_user=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL', 'RATING_MEAN','RATING_STD', 'RATING_MIN', 'RATING_MAX', 'RATING_COUNT']
    df_fact_hotel = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns_fact_user)

    df_fact_hotel['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL'] = helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().index
    df_fact_hotel['RATING_MEAN'] =          helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL')['REVIEWS_RATING'].mean().values
    df_fact_hotel['RATING_STD'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].std().values
    df_fact_hotel['RATING_MIN'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].min().values
    df_fact_hotel['RATING_MAX'] =           helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].max().values
    df_fact_hotel['RATING_COUNT'] =         helper.groupby(by='DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL', as_index=True)['REVIEWS_RATING'].count().values
    df_fact_hotel.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)
    
    # fact_rating_2
    df_fact_rating_2 = pd.merge(df_fact_rating, df_dim_hotel, how='left', suffixes=('', '_h'),
                            left_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_HOTEL'], right_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'])

    df_fact_rating_2 = pd.merge(df_fact_rating_2, df_dim_user, how='left', suffixes=('', '_u'),
                            left_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_USER'], right_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'])

    df_fact_rating_2 = pd.merge(df_fact_rating_2, df_dim_state, how='left', suffixes=('', '_s'),
                            left_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE'], right_on=['DW_ID_HASH_KEY'])

    df_fact_rating_2 = pd.merge(df_fact_rating_2, df_dim_cal, how='left', 
                            left_on=['REVIEWS_DATE'], right_on=['CLDR_DATE'])

    df_fact_rating_2.drop(['DW_ID_HASH_KEY_h','DW_ID_HASH_KEY_STATE_h','DW_ID_HASH_KEY_u','DW_ID_HASH_KEY_s'],axis=1,inplace=True)
    df_fact_rating_2.columns
    
    # connect to the database, db file will be gyg.db
    conn = sqlite3.connect('gyg.db')
    
    df_fact_rating.to_sql('df_fact_rating', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_fact_rating_2.to_sql('df_fact_rating_2', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_fact_hotel.to_sql('df_fact_hotel', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_fact_user.to_sql('df_fact_user', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_fact_state.to_sql('df_fact_state', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_dim_user.to_sql('df_dim_user', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_dim_hotel.to_sql('df_dim_hotel', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_dim_state.to_sql('df_dim_state', conn, if_exists='replace')
    df_dim_cal.to_sql('df_dim_cal', conn, if_exists='replace')
    
    print('All tables were written in gyg.db file.')
In [41]:
data_pipeline(df, df_states)
